review_blob: Pours light brown, dark red. Smells sweet of caramel, vanilla and Candi sugar. Tastes thick with a lot of sweetness, hints of apple, molasses, a bit of peat, and almost no alcohol.
beer_name: Anchorage A Deal With The Devil Barleywine

review_blob: Bottle from Belmont Station. Pours dark brown with tan foam. Smells sweet of vanilla, chocolate, and alcohol. Tastes sweet, full-bodied, roasty (some chocolate and coffee) with a hint of rum.
beer_name: 10 Barrel / Bluejacket / Stone Suede Imperial Porter

review_blob: Bottle from Jay. Pours dark brown/black with mocha brown foam. Smells strongly of alcohol, coffee and cedar. Tastes earthy of coffee, cinnamon, cocoa, peanuts and alcohol.

Bottle from Colorado! Pours black with dark brown/mocha foam. Smells sweet, rich of chocolate, vanilla, caramel and a bit of coffee. Tastes sweet, thick, sticky, alcohol, toffee, chocolate, vanilla, creme brule, coffee.

Bottle from jay. Pours a thin dark brown with dark brown foam. Smells slightly sweet with hints of vanilla, bourbon, chocolate and a hint of coffee. Tastes roasty, with a surprising amount of tannins, hints of coffee, vanilla, and bit of root beer.

Bottle from Belmont station with Lars. Pours a cloudy medium brown with yellowish foam. Smells extremely sour with vinegar, herbs, cherry and almost a little chocolate. Tastes very sour with some vinegar and red wine notes and sour cherry with old wood.

Bottle from jay. Pours a thin dark brown with tan foam. Smells lightly sweet of vanilla, butterscotch, and a touch of dark fruit. Tastes thin with coffee, a touch of raspberries, chocolate and a mike sour.

Bottle from Jay. Pours dark/medium brown with tan foam. Smells rich and sweet of caramel, molasses, and a touch of anise. Tastes initially very different from the nose, very bitter and not terribly sweet, but as you wait, or introduce air, the sweetness comes through with raison, molasses and dark caremel.
Bottle from Jay with Willi. Pours a hazy gold with a nice lingering off white foam. Smells resinous of citrus caramel and sweet barley. Tastes sweet with alcohol, citrus and a hint of nuttiness.
Bottle from Jay with Jake. Pours red/purple with minimal off white foam. Smells very tart of lemon and raspberry. Tastes very tart/sour of raspberry, and a touch of lemon.
Bottle from brewery. Pours red/gold with off white foam. Smells sweet and bitter with hints citrus. Medium body with a fair bitterness and mile nuttiness.
Bottle from jay. Pours dark brown with milk chocolate foam. Smells hints of vanilla, coffee, oak and bourbon. Tastes sweet with a touch of honey, vanilla, bourbon, chocolate and a touch of coffee.
Bottle from Belmont station with Willi. Pours brown with off white foam. Smells of citric acid, cherries, and earthy oak. Tastes sharp and sour of lemon, earth, cherries and sharp alcohol.
beer_name: Anchorage / Crooked Stave Between the Staves

review_blob: Bottle from brewery with Willi. Pours a slightly hazy gold with off white foam. Smells sweet and fruity of grapefruit, apricot, peach and cranberry. Tastes nicely bitter with mild citrus and hints of earth, grapefruit and funk.
Bottle from brewery with Andrew and Carter. Pours black with tan foam. Smells sweet of chocolate, vanilla and bourbon. Tastes harsh with lots of chocolate and bourbon. Would be great aged.

Can from Jay. Pours a hazy orange/gold/yellow with nice off white foam. Smells earthy and yeasty, a little tropical with a hint of lemon and carbon dioxide. Tastes a little nutty and fairly malty, has a pretty diverse hop start, but it fades to just plain bitter with a touch of alcohol at the end. Really didnt live up to the hype, though it is a solid IPA.
Bottle from north Carolina. pours thick and black. Smells thick and sweet of vanilla and raison. Tastes thick, sweet of raison, peat, and a little bourbon.
On trap at brewery. Pours a lightly hazy amber red. Smells strongly of site cherries and lemon. Tastes sour of cherries with a hint of wood. Nice and tart, though not terribly complex.
On tap at brewery. Pours a dark amber with off-white foam. Smells set and malty. Tastes sweet with a nice dark fruit and a hunt is bourbon.
Bottle at sandy beverages. Pours a lightly hazy light gold with nice white foam. Smells sweet and tasty of peach and wheat. Tastes wheaty with lots of clove

Bottle from Belmont station with Willi. Pours clear gold with white foam. Smells sweet with hints wheat, citrus and smoked wood. Tastes sweet and slightly peppery with mild smoke, general earthy tones, no alcohol burn and a surprising bitterness.
beer_name: Stone Matts Burning Rosids Imperial Cherry Wood Smoked Saison

review_blob: Bottle from Belmont Station. Pours dark brown bordering on black with tan foam. Smells earthy of coffee and chocolate. Tastes fully and earthy with hints of peat, coffee, chocolate, prunes and peppery hops.

beer_brewer_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
review_blob: Bottle from brewery. Put a murky red/brown with no foam at all. Smells sweet of bourbon, oak, apple, butter and hints of cinnamon. Tastes all but flat and relatively thin with hints of apple, cinnamon, brown sugar, bourbon and milk chocolate.
beer_name: Hair of the Dog Pannepooch Reserva

review_blob: UPDATED: MAR 7, 2014
Bottle from beer mongers. Pours dark brown with tan foam. Smells of coffee and chocolate with briny and earthy tones. Tastes bitter, slightly sweet with hints of chocolate, coffee and a little salt.
beer_name: New Belgium The Trip XIX (Taylor Shellfish Farms Oyster Stout)

review_blob: Bottle from Belmont Station. Pours dark brown with almost no foam. Smells lightly sweet, oaky, slight vanilla and a bit of alcohol. Tastes full bodied, with hints of dark fruits, vanilla, a bit of chocolateand ends with a big alcohol burn.
On tap at brewery. Pours hold with fine white foam. Smells crisp and clean with a mild bitter pine. Tastes set and luponic with hints of pine and set grapefruit.
Pour from Bridgetown. Pours super dark. I cant judge the smell from the sterilization of the glass. Tastes very sweet with tons of brown sugar and ginger and bourbon.
beer_name: The Bruery Black Tuesday Imperial Stout

review_blob: On task at ecliptic. Or dark brown with tan foam. Smells sweet of marshmallows, vanilla and chocolate. tastes sweet, but feels dry, hints of coffee dark chocolate and cherry.

Bottle from new seasons. Pours black with light tan foam. Smells crisp slightly sweet with hints of ice cream. Tastes oddly milky and roasty with hints of chocolate and coffee. I really dont get any salt or caramel.

Bottle from Jay with Willi. Pours black with tan foam. Smells sweet and lightly boozy with lots of vanilla and sweet coffee. Tastes chocolaty and fittingly thin with plenty of vanilla and ends with oak and coffee.
beer_name: Triple C Up All Night Breakfast Porter - Bourbon Barrel

review_blob: Growler from tin bucket with Willi. Or mildly hazy copper with white foam. Smells slightly tart and sweet of honey and a little cherry. Tastes of sour cherries, mild wheat and a little salt.
Bottle from Belmont station with Willi. Pours ruby red with white foam. Smells warm of what, berries and a hint of oak. Tastes sweet and tart of lingonberries, currents and a surprising body.
UPDATED: MAR 13, 2014
beer_name: New Belgium / Cigar City Lips of Faith - Anaheim & Marash Chili Ale

review_blob: Bottle from Belmont Station. Pours opaque black with dark tan foam. Smells sweet of vanilla and chocolate with hints of butter, bacon, coffee and a little alcohol burn. Tastes sweet of raison, chili, chocolate and mild coffee.

Bottle from New Seasons. Pours a clear gold with white foam. Smells of sweet citrusy lupulin and malts. Tastes surprisingly light, and floral with some subtle grapefruit, drier than the nose suggests.

Bottle from Belmont Station. Pours a hazy orange/gold with tons of frothy yellow/tan foam. Smells earthy and wild with hints of grapefruit, cinnamon, cedar, peach and pineapple. Has medium body and has flavors all over the board ranging from pineapple/grapefruit to cardamom, clove and black pepper, and thats not to forget the general bite of this beer, its bitter through and through.
Bottle from jay with Jake. Pours dark brown with frothy tan foam. Smells strongly of bourbon with hints of sweet vanilla. Tastes thin of bourbon, smoked meat and is surprisingly buttery.
On tap at tin bucket with Willi. Pours jet black with task foam. Smells super roasty of coffee. Tastes medium thick with lots of earthy coffee and a hint of cedar.

Bottle from Superior Liquor. Pours a lightly hazy light orange/gold. Smells subtle of honey, honeybush, orange and sweetbread. Decent mouthfeel. Tastes mildly of alcohol with a lot of honey/sweetbread sweetness and ends surprisingly bitter.

Bottle from Belmont Station. Pours slightly hazy amber/gold with off-white foam. Smells warm with a hint of pine. Tastes mild, slightly sweet of very mild lemonaid, finishes with more body than expect, slightly wheaty, slightly red.
Bottle at Bridgetown. Smells strongly of raison and a hint of bourbon. Tastes sweet and boozey, delicious.
On tap at Bridgetown. Pours gold with off-white foam. Smells generally green with a hint of sweet barley. Tastes sticky and tingly of lots of hoods and alcohol.
Bottle with Willi. Smells sweet and slightly dry of caramel and fresh wort. Tastes dry and surprisingly hoppy, with maybe a hint of oak. Really not a Porter at all, more of a red.
Bottle with Jake. Pours a amber/red with off-white foam. Smells sweet of grapefruit and a hint if pine. Tastes sweet of grapefruit, peach and pine and has a solid bitter end.
beer_name: Ninkasi Dawn of the Red India Red Ale

review_blob: Bottle from Belmont station. Pours dark brown with tan foam. Smells mildly of coffee with hints of pine and grass. Tastes surprisingly thick and bitter with hints of dusty chocolate, coffee and pecans.

Bottle from Jay. Pours a thick black with super dense long-lasting tan foam. Smells sweet of rootbeer, and slightly sour of chocolate. Body is creamy like a thin milk stout and tastes sweet and sour with hints of coffee, vanilla, and licorice and ends bitter of hops.

Bottle from Jay. Pours a thick, opaque black/brown with dark mocha foam. Smells strongly of earthy java/coffee with a hint of spice/caffeine. Tastes surprisingly mild, not quite as thick as I was expecting, sweet of dark chocolate, which fades into coffee and ends slightly bitter with a lot of coffee trailing on forever. Would be amazing with breakfast, is amazing with a turkey dinner.
beer_name: Terrapin Wake-n-Bake Coffee Oatmeal Imperial Stout

review_blob: Bottle from Belmont Station. Pours a lightly hazy amber with off-white foam. Smells sweet, mild of barley and caramel. Tastes like a combination of a red and a mild barleywine, with a slight nuttiness, a hint of rose grapes and a touch of alcohol.

Bottle from Belmont Station. Pours a beautiful gold with white foam. Smells crisp, sweet, spicy and slightly citrusy. Surprisingly full bodied. Tastes sweet, lemony, piney and more balanced than Id expect from Stone.
